# Extension UI: button hover and active states

Aligned with **[DESIGN.md](../../DESIGN.md)** (hard offset shadows, HUD tactility). **Every `<button>`** (and **`label.btn`** file pickers) in **`apps/extension`** must give clear **`:hover`** and **`:active`** feedback—not a static control that only changes on `:focus-visible`.

## Default: use `.btn`

- Prefer **`tailwind.css`** **`@layer components`** classes **`btn`**, **`btn primary`**, **`btn ghost`**, plus **`icon-only`** / **`sm`** as needed. Those selectors **must** keep matching **`:hover`** and **`:active`** rules in the same file (see **`tailwind-btn-states.test.ts`**).
- **`aria-pressed`** / toggles for open overlays (e.g. Settings dialog): inactive = **`btn ghost`**, active = **`btn primary`** unless a one-off design needs different pairing—still use **`btn`** variants so states stay centralized.

## Exceptions (custom classes)

If a control **cannot** use **`btn`** (e.g. full-width **`role="menuitem"`** rows, **`linkish`** text buttons):

- Add Tailwind **`hover:*`** and **`active:*`** utilities (background, opacity, shadow, or color)—**both**—or define **`@layer components`** hooks in **`tailwind.css`** (as with **`.linkish`**).
- **`transition-*`** on a short **`duration-100`** keeps presses from flashing.

## Do not

- Ship a plain **`<button className="…">`** with only layout/typography and no hover/active (keyboard **`:focus-visible`** alone is not enough for pointer users).
- Rely on browser default button chrome; extension UI is fully styled.
